On the 23rd December 2021, the NOWA National President, Hajiya Nana Aisha Gambo commissioned the Naval Officers Wives Association Centre for skills acquisitions in Headquarters Logistics Command Oghara, Delta State. For her, this center would help women to contribute tirelessly to the growth of not just the state but the country at large as well. Speaking about this development she shared that, “Our project is for humanity, so it’s for both officers wives and the community at large. Through this we ensure not just our officers wives benefit from our projects but every woman in the community too which is what we always do.” The centre comprises of a conference room and a hall, as well as a skill acquisition centre open to both the Naval and host community. This project was achieved with the support of the Flag Officer Commanding Logistics Command, Rear Admiral SS Lassa.